name: ▼Prologue
note: <NoBookData>

name: Dark Soul
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Darkness Monster
Mainly lives in the Seat of Creation

A being that emerges from the great darkness.
Instinctively seeks out the true night,
one that doesn't exist in this world.>

name: Born in the Dark, Kaamos
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア,boss>
<text:Darkness Spirit
Encountered in the Seat of Creation

The Great Darkness that Wanders 
Behind the Stars. Its steps dye 
the pure earth black.

Her actions held no malice,
betraying but a maddening desire.>

name: ▼Ront
note: <NoBookData>

name: Romun
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Rat Monster
Mostly appears in the Mountains of Auli

A large rat found in mountainous areas.
It has sharp claws, and although it is 
dangerous, it does not actively attack.>

name: Stonebug
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Insect Monster
Mainly lives in the Mountains of Auli

There is a debate circulating around it.
Is it a buglike rock, or a rocklike bug?
Either way, it's hard, for real.>

name: Poleon
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Lion Monster
Mainly lives in the Mountains of Auli

A lion is mighty and noble,
qualities none can replicate easily.

It may be small, but it is still a lion.
Those who let their guard down is in
for a harsh reality check.>

name: Colruka
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Little Monster
Mainly lives in the Mountains of Auli

A type of monster called a Barbarian.
Good with hands, strong in arms, and smart.
They use their talent to create various crafts.

Has a strong libido.>

name: Peak of Auli
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント,boss>
<text:Deer Monster
Encountered in the Mountains of Auli

A huge beast that can be mistaken for a 
mountain. It is the king of mountains, 
likened to a peak.

The beast was born and lived in Ront all 
its life. And as such, it was given the 
name: "Auli".>

name: Wolfspider
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Spider Monster
Mainly lives in the Village Cemetery.

The wolf spider grabs opponents with its 
entire body. Alone, they may not pose a 
threat, but when they appear in groups, 
they are a deadly group.>

name: Bloomoa
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Plant Monster
Mainly lives in the Village Cemetery.

An abominable flower that grows in a 
nursery of corpses. Although it is disliked 
as an ominous existence that symbolizes 
death, in fact it is a symbol of rebirth.>

name: Hundread
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Centipede Monster
Mainly lives in the Village Cemetery.

Insects with a hundred legs and a long body.
It appears they can also be used as arms.
They are also capable of using tools.>

name: Rock Smasher Centipede
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント,boss>
<text:Centipede Monster
Encountered in the Village Cemetery

A very grown-up centipede.
It was more than the size of a man.

After the master died, the centipedes 
remained, but they seem to have stopped 
disturbing the Barbarians.>

name: Pistolfish
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Fish Monster
Mainly lives in the Stagnant Basin.

A monster that swims while storing water.
It shoots it out like bullets in combat.
Its power can pierce shoddy shields,
and even scrapes iron sometimes.>

name: Musico
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Fish Monster
Mainly lives in the Stagnant Basin.

Water that has obtained a nucleus
and started drifting in the air.
Just a harmless monster, as long as
you don't get too close.>

name: Jelly Mary
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Liquid Monster
Mainly lives in the Stagnant Basin.

A liquid monster storing excessive Mana,
taking on a form optimized for it.
In this form, they approach humans
with a more aggressive nature.>

name: Floater
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Ghost Monster
Mainly lives in the Village Well.

Smoke-like ghost.
Difficult to strike with physical weapons,
try using Wind and Light instead.>

name: Hildhill
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Leech Monster
Mainly lives in the Village Well.

If you move along some waterway, getting
it stuck on you is almost a given.
Leeches are like that, after all.
Some people immediately faints upon
spotting a huge leech on their leg.>

name: That Which Lies Under The Stream
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント,boss>
<text:Water Monster
Encountered in the Village Well

From the accounts of the monsters, it is
something which appears frequently,
causing damage in its wake.

However, she never hurt anything.
To honor her old friend Barnu, she 
stands trial for those who wish to depart.>

name: Roaromun
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Rat Monster
Mainly lives in Tantali of Departure

A subspecies of Romun. Very ferocious.
In battle, it can only scratch,
but its movements are efficient and swift.>

name: Hutlis
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Squirrel Monster
Mainly lives in Tantali of Departure

A plump and fat squirrel.
Always rests sitting on its tail.

When fighting, it charges lazily.
Quite powerful due to its weight.>

name: Holstina
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Cow Monster
Mainly lives in Tantali of Departure

Their voluptuous bodies and incredible 
strength is so that they can perform 
their work efficiently. 

When they are outside, they eagerly seek out 
males as if that is their reason for living.
>

name: Chargeboar
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Pig Monster
Mainly lives in Tantali of Departure

Extremely shortsighted monsters. 
To them, unknown creatures are enemies. 
Enemies are beings that must be defeated. 

They don't understand conversation. 
It's best to respond with force.>

name: Merolin Dog
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Dog Monster
Mainly lives in Tantali of Departure

They are very similar to dogs.
Friendly, obedient after gaining their trust, 
and above all, they have adorable behaviors.

Not very intelligent.>

name: Accursed Ritual
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント,boss>
<text:Wand Monster
Encountered in Tantali of Departure

A talisman created through repeated rituals.
The blighted symbol of the old Ront.

The Sorcerer thought they were commanding
the wand, but it was the opposite in reality.>

name: Barculegg
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Centipede Monster
Mainly lives in Centipede Road

A centipede discolored by its own venom.
This happens naturally when it grows,
but some cannot withstand that venom.>

name: Necroweed
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Plant Monster
Mainly lives in Centipede Road

A flower that grows from a corpse,
and is thus influenced by it.
It is said that it lures onlookers to death,
but it's safe as long as you don't touch it.

You'll die if you do.>

name: Grippers
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Spider Monster
Mainly lives in the Underground Castle.

It grabs its opponent with its whole body.
This action creates a large opening and
is largely fatal to insect haters.>

name: Skullrope
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Bone Monster
Mainly lives in the Underground Castle.

A being made up of scattered bones.
Snake-like, but not made of snake bones.

Why the bones are connected is unknown.
Perhaps they have a sense of unity?>

name: Bloodball
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Water Monster
Mainly lives in the Underground Castle.

Blood that seems to have a core and 
has begun to move. The way it gushes out 
of the wounds of those who have fallen 
is extremely eerie and horrifying.>

name: Queen of Solitude
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント,boss>
<text:Ant Monster
Encountered in the Underground Castle

When the castle stood tall in Tantali,
the queen was a symbol of prosperity.

Now, its authority has sunk underground
alongside this castle, due to the
machinations of those Sorcerers.>

name: Luora's Darkness
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント,boss>
<text:Army of the Night
Encountered in Thicket Tower

Luora once lost her place in the world 
due to a certain incident.

That's why she chose a new path 
from which she could never return.>

name: ▼ロント1.10
note: <NoBookData>

name: Endromun
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Rat Monster
Mainly lives in Hauskaa Forest

A subspecies of Romun. Very ferocious.
In battle, it can only scratch,
but its movements are efficient and swift.>

name: Ratroka
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Little Monster
Mainly lives in Hauskaa Forest

A type of monster called a Barbarian.
Good with hands, strong in arms, and smart.
They use their talent to create various crafts.

Has a strong libido.>

name: Whirlwoof
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Dog Monster
Mainly lives in Hauskaa Forest

A blue-skinned dog monster.
It's wary and hard to get to open up,
but you can win it over with patience.

Surprisingly clever, 
but not beyond imagination.>

name: Demonmarn
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Cow Monster
Mainly lives in Hauskaa Forest

A cow monster that is also demon-type.
With its incredible strength, it wields 
its tree-like weapon and deliver a
blow that can reshape the terrain.>

name: Trivast
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント>
<text:Dog Monster
Mainly lives in Hauskaa Forest

A terrifying monster known as a Demon Dog.
Have breasts that can be mistaken for heads.

Many are violent, but some can be easily
talked to and may even become affectionate.>

name: Ultimate Dog
note: <NoBookData>

name: Ultimate Barbarian
note: <NoBookData>

name: Ultimate Demon Dog
note: <NoBookData>

name: Ultimate Kotama
note: <NoBookData>

name: Reflection of Reason
note: <NoBookData>

name: Creation's Evolution, Unelma
note:
<CategoryKey:ロント,boss>
<text:That Which Lives On The Star
Encountered at Unelma of the Ultimate

Since the star's birth, Unelma was there,
changing her form with the times.

Its current form is temporary,
but it seems to like it aplenty.>

name: Ultimate Ninja Owl
note: <NoBookData>

name: Ultimate Succubus
note: <NoBookData>

name: Ultimate Shark
note: <NoBookData>

name: Ultimate Scylla
note: <NoBookData>

name: Ultimate Chimera
note: <NoBookData>

name: ▼Kertailt
note: <NoBookData>

name: Toothleaf
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Flower Monster
Mostly appears in the Spirit Forest.

It pretends to be harmless despite
its numerous fangs and huge body.
Few are ever convinced.>

name: Suzulamp
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Flower Monster
Mostly appears in the Spirit Forest.

A ferocius but useful monster.
It stores the Thunder attribute and
uses it to shine light into the dark.>

name: Floscros
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Flower Monster
Mostly appears in the Spirit Forest.

A female monster living in the forest.
It was once believed to be a Fairy.

Usually laid-back, but also has a
lustful side.>

name: Carteret
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Bat Monster
Mostly appears in the Spirit Forest.

Bat monsters prefer darkness.
However, that doesn't mean it itself
possesses the Dark attribute.>

name: Malmal
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Multipede Monster
Mostly appears in the Opysitri Habitat.

A large crustacean that appears in caves.
While rolling and moving, its movement 
stores electricity in its body.>

name: Opysitri
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Snake Woman Monster
Mostly appears in the Opysitri Habitat.

A race that keeps to themselves,
with an infamous sadistic mind.
Do not approach habitat.

People say that the ones called Opysel
are gentle, but it's just a rumor 
and is hard to believe.>

name: Abomination of Opysos
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト,boss>
<text:Snake Monster
Encountered in the Opysitri Habitat

An ugly poison-spewing Snake Woman.
She lives alone away from others.

She definitely must've been loathed,
says the ignorant ridicules.>
<反撃拡張:毒カウンター>

name: Lambiglio
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Insect Monster
Mostly appears in the Lavenderie Nursery.

A monster that stores the Light attribute
as its life force. Those with more life
shine more brightly.>

name: Rivilaska
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Weasel Monster
Mostly appears in the Lavenderie Nursery.

It has a somewhat feminine physique, 
but there are also male individuals.

Its tail can be used as a weapon, 
but is usually for intimidation.>

name: Camostrider
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Lizard Monster
Mostly appears in the Lavenderie Nursery.

Its body color changes with temperature,
making it difficult to find despite
its massive size, even in battle.>

name: Spotted Mushroom
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Mushroom Monster
Mostly appears in Lavenderie Nursery.

A ferocious mushroom, and active cause
of death in the deep forests.
Its powder causes bruising on touch,
and death on continued inhaling.>

name: Dustlooter
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Trashdigging Monster
Mostly appears in Lavenderie Nursery.

Scavenging garbage is its sole purpose.
It piles them up and creates a unique
work of art, a special residence.
It stinks, but that helps it
repel other monsters away.>

name: Seed of Original Sin, Mollu
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト,boss>
<text:Insect Monster
Encountered at Lavenderie Nursery.

A deformed Mollu, who's sucked up a
great amount of Mana. Its ego still
persists through the changes.

There once was a parasite known as
the Original Sin, who devoured many
worlds defying all logic. Perhaps
this is its return...?>

name: Shining Phantom, Valco
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト,boss>
<text:Lord of Reason
Encountered at the Thunder Tree.

The Wolf Spirit of Kertailt, who watches
over the residents without interfering.

It is no cold-hearted being, indeed.
It believes in the power to live.>

name: Kotama
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Mysterious Monster
Mainly lives in the Forest Outskirts

A strange-looking being.
It is said to be a type of spirit
that brings small blessings to those
who have encountered it.>

name: Mutated Thunder Root
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト,boss>
<text:Plant Monster
Encountered in the Forest Outskirts

The Thunder Tree buries roots in the Star.
It absorbs the remnants of Mana,
stores it, and eventually returns it.
Monsters may be born from this process.

This is a distortion of Kertailt.
It absolutely must be destroyed.>

name: Devourio
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Insect Monster
Mainly lives in Spiral City

A monster that stores Light as life force.
The healthier the individual,
the brighter its light shines.>

name: Bimalmal
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Multi-legged Monster
Mainly lives in Spiral City

A crustacean charged with lightning.
It uses its power to roll erratically
while also discharging electricity, 
causing damage over a wide area.>

name: Madcap
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Little Monster
Mainly lives in Spiral City

A type of monster known as a Barbarian.
They explore dangerous areas in search 
of rare items, and as a result
their combat prowess is high.

Males with excessive sexual desires 
are not killed, but captured alive.>

name: Ghoula
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Corpse Monster
Mainly lives in Spiral City

A corpse activated by lightning.
Possesses reasonable intelligence 
and great magical power to boot.

Ghoula eats human flesh, and
considers adventurers as food.>

name: Mushrope
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Mushroom Monster
Mainly lives in Mushroom Village Cieni

It looks just like a giant mushroom,
but Mushropes rarely camouflages.
In most cases, they just wander around.>

name: Donbarone
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Mushroom Monster
Mainly lives in Mushroom Village Cieni

A mushroom monster with great strength,
a common result of a Mushrope's growth.

Surprisingly kind-hearted.>

name: Manitari Kyria
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Mushroom Monster
Mainly lives in Mushroom Village Cieni

A mushroom monster with fascinating
appearance, a possible result of
a Mushrope's growth.

It is well aware of its own beauty.
It is said that it does not mimic
other creatures, but many still
persist in this belief.>

name: Mushrage
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト,boss>
<text:Mushroom Monster
Encountered in Mushroom Village Cieni

A burning mushroom.
Looks like a Mushrope, but could
also be a different species.
Normally, Mushropes die when burned.

It's probably hot.
It writhes around violently.>

name: Libelamp
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Flower Monster
Mainly lives in Thunder Tree Shroud.

A monster with Thunder attribute light.
It casts it as a spell upon its enemies,
and sometimes on non-enemies as well.>

name: Flagleon
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Lion Monster
Mainly lives in Thunder Tree Shroud.

A lion with a distinctive mane. 
It looks more like petals than feathers. 
In battles with its kind, the vividness 
of its color determines its superiority.>

name: Rosemaria
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト>
<text:Flower Monster
Mainly lives in Thunder Tree Shroud.

A demonic flower that contains neurotoxins.
Looks pretty, but has a cruel personality, 
slowly torturing its opponents
after immobilizing them.>

name: Warlord of the Night, Mollu
note:
<CategoryKey:ケルタイルト,boss>
<text:Army of the Night
Encountered at the Thunder Tree

The Mollu that parasitized the 
Thunder Tree, wielding its full power.

This was originally that empty land
that eventually became the universe.>

name: ▼Talvirar
note: <NoBookData>

name: Cottontop
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Cotton Monster
Mainly lives in the Snow Hunting Fields

Cottontops' true identity is unknown.
Whether it's a plant monster or other,
nothing is known about it.

Goes bald when exposed to strong winds.>

name: Penguile
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Bird Monster
Mainly lives in the Snow Hunting Fields

A strange bird that lives in cold regions. 
It can't fly, but it's good at swimming. 

It seems slow at a glance, but it
glides across the ice at high speeds
when on the hunt.>

name: Grayshalta
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Ice Monster
Mainly lives in the Snow Hunting Fields

A being similar to a spirit.
It appears when the ambient Mana 
contains attributes of the land.

This one is Ice attribute.>

name: Skullmer
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Fish Monster
Mainly lives in the Snow Hunting Fields

It's supposed to be a fish monster, 
but it's more of a bone monster 
or maybe a corpse monster. 
It's a confusing thing.>

name: Snow Mary
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Liquid Monster
Mainly lives in the Snow Hunting Fields

A liquid monster storing excessive Mana,
taking on a form optimized for it.
In this form, they approach humans
with a more aggressive nature.>

name: Nekonchu Hunter
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル,boss>
<text:Cat Monster
Encountered in the Snow Hunting Grounds

A large Nekonchu that become a hunter.
Lives for its friends on the frozen star.

Its carefree personality contrasts its
top notch hunting skills. Be on guard.>

name: Escapee of Lavigny
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル,boss>
<text:Mystery Monster
Encountered in the Snow Hunting Fields

In the early days of Talvirar, 
the people were all family. 
They had a bond that went beyond blood. 

Those bonds were absolute, and 
betrayal was not tolerated.>

name: Clapper
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Bomb Monster
Mainly lives in the Alien Ruins

A type of unexploded bomb.
Explodes on the slightest impact.

They shouldn't cause harm when ignored,
but they can fall over and explode on
their own, so it's best to simply
dispose of them once you find them.>

name: Oildrip
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Liquid Monster
Mainly lives in the Alien Ruins

A monster born from the Mana of spilt oil.
Extremely weak to fire, but strangely
enough, it also uses fire magic.
Such bravery.>

name: Elem
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Liquid Monster
Mainly lives in the Alien Ruins

A female Oildrip. 
Stronger, but still weak to fire.

She has a curious personality and will 
slowly follow anything that moves, 
even if that thing is a fire.>

name: Wraith of the Laboratory
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル,boss>
<text:Ghost Monster
Encountered in the Alien Ruins

The ghost that believed in promises
and continued to kill in its name.
He's not even aware of his own death.

He thought he was a collector,
but he was just another material.>

name: Dead Block
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Rubble Monster
Mainly lives in the Tower of Knowledge

It's said to be a rubble monster,
but it's actually a black stain that
wraps itself around rubble to hide.

It ended up standing out even more.>

name: Freezeforge
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Mana Monster
Mainly lives in the Tower of Knowledge

Mana that is formed by magic itself,
a type of magical creature.

It's rare for such things to be
born naturally. In most cases, you
can expect a Magician nearby.>

name: Bookworm
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Insect Monster
Mainly lives in the Tower of Knowledge

Looks like a book monster, but actually 
is a bug monster that lives in books. 
It especially likes magic books.

Mastered the magic held within.>

name: Witchnoel
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Humanoid Monster
Mainly lives in the Tower of Knowledge

The origin of the title of Magician.
Can use a wide variety of magic.

Intelligent and easy to talk to,
but will not listen to idiots.>

name: Tangleshadow
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Shadow Monster
Mainly lives in the Locked Fortress

Shadow monsters have been known since 
the age of myth, so few people 
are unaware of them.

They have the ability to freely enter 
and exit the shadows, and sometimes 
even drag their enemies into it.>

name: Amkrite
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Shadow Monster
Mainly lives in the Locked Fortress

Most monsters have female counterparts
with similar characteristics. This
is to obtain more Mana for themselves.

Amkrite is one such monster with a
special organ to more efficiently
extract Mana from men.>

name: Distortion of Lunacy
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル,boss>
<text:Darkness Monster
Encountered in the Snow Hunting Fields

A monster born from Dark influence.
It heralds madness and lunacy.

This itself is the nature of the night.
However, this world has forgotten
the terror of the Dark.>

name: Clawrian
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Humanoid Monster
Mainly lives in Lavigny of Bondings

The way it crawls about is reminiscent
of a baby. Very creepy and disgusting.
It is said that this is a behavior
intended to lower the opponent's guard,
but it's just counterproductive.>

name: Passest
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Ghost Monster
Mainly lives in Lavigny of Bondings

A strange ghost that possesses weapons 
and freely manipulates them to 
perform physical attacks.

Drops its weapon in strong winds.>

name: Curspot
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Nest Monster
Mainly lives in Lavigny of Bondings

A monster that looks like a nest. 
Sometimes it is, sometimes it isn't. 
When Mana is stored inside, 
something will seek to live in it.>

name: Auribile of Embrace
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル,boss>
<text:Viscera Monster
Encountered in Lavigny of Bondings

A monster known as an Auribile.
Slimy like viscera and covered in blood.

When the Mana of multiple lifeforms 
mix together, their existence usually 
breaks down and they die. 
But when this doesn't happen, 
a grotesque being is born.>

name: Asherma
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Fish Monster
Mainly lives in Lavigny Barricade Prison

A corpse fish floating in the air.
It's unsure why they float, but
that's just the usual with the dead.>

name: Polscien
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Octopus Monster
Mainly lives in Lavigny Barricade Prison

A monster with strong magical power.
Has octopus tentacles and dog ears.

Hard to fight head on. It's best to
attack it with Thunder attacks.>

name: Monstrosity of the Barricade Prison
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル>
<text:Mystery Monster
Wanders in Lavigny Barricade Prison

When the land was united, these monsters
were parents who loved everyone.

Perhaps they still are, punishing
those children who make mistakes.>

name: Muracca's Darkness
note:
<CategoryKey:タルヴィラル,boss>
<text:Army of the Night
Encountered in Lavigny

Muracca had nothing left to lose,
and as such no attachment to the world.

Being unable to return was a relief.
It meant she can only look forward,
that is what she believed.>

name: ▼Torion
note: <NoBookData>

name: Lavarock
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Insect Monster
Mainly lives in the Flame Cemetery

A rock-like insect living in magma.
Its surface burns on the touch.>

name: Malballoon
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Balloon Monster
Mainly lives in the Flame Cemetery

A balloon-like monster filled with
poisonous gas. It floats in the air
and occasionally crashes into you,
but otherwise poses no threat.

Do not pop under any circumstances.>
<反撃拡張:破裂カウンター>

name: Baby Dran
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Dragon Monster
Mainly lives in the Flame Cemetery

Dragons are considered special among 
monsters, their majestic appearance 
inspiring awe upon witnesses.
Even baby dragons are no exception.>

name: Mogwurm
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Insect Monster
Mainly lives in the Flame Cemetery

A giant insect that swims in magma.
Stores lava inside its body and spits
it out to burn all in its path.>

name: Magma Dragonfish
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン,boss>
<text:Fish Monster
Encountered at the Flame Cemetery

A giant fish with an armor-like shell,
known as the feared Dragonfish.

It seems to be overheating.
Did it eat something bad?>

name: Tetra Device
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Machine Monster
Mainly lives in the Entertainment District

A mechanical guardian that fell from
the Sky Ruins. It has lost sight of
what it was meant to protect, and now
guards the place where it fell.>

name: Drivern
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Machine Monster
Mainly lives in the Entertainment District

A machine functioning as a vehicle.
Transforms into such a form when in use.

It utilizes its mobility during battle.
Stay calm when dealing with it.>

name: Formole
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Mole Monster
Mainly lives in the Entertainment District

A small monster that lurks underground.
It digs into any location and
carves open its own path.>

name: Archenemy
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Insect Monster
Mainly lives in the Entertainment District

The nemesis of mankind.
No explanation needed.>

name: Murder Maiden
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Humanoid Monster
Mainly lives in Decadent Street

This monster lives to kill.
No one knows the reason for this.
One would think it is for Mana,

but in reality, it's a simple reason.
It's for its own sexual desire.>

name: Nymphomane
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Succubus Monster
Mainly lives in Succubus Street

Succubi prefer Mana from males.
Thus, males must be especially careful.

An unsatisfied Succubus is like a
rogue beast. If you're not a woman,
run, and run far.>

name: Fremane
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Succubus Monster
Mainly lives in Succubus Street

Succubi prefer male Mana,
but some do target women sometimes.
I'm sure there's some like that.>

name: Succubus of the 7th Administration
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン,boss>
<text:Succubus Monster
Encountered in the 7th Admin. Building

Though she is an old Succubus,
her beauty is unblemished. She exudes
a sultry allure lacking in the young.

Men cannot reason with her.
Fight Succubi with Succubi.>

name: Team Merolins
note: <NoBookData>

name: Succulent Flowers
note: <NoBookData>

name: Saber in Red
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン,boss>
<text:Unknown Swordsman
Encountered at Hersteide

The true identity of this swordsman
is indeed Ront's Lord of Reason.
Her extraordinary strength ruins
the festival and dismays its organizer.

There's nothing more boring than
a match whose outcome is decided.
The value of true camaraderie,
this Luora knows well.>

name: Flareforge
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Mana Monster
Mainly lives in Fire Dragon Mountain

Mana that is formed by magic itself,
a type of magical creature.

It rarely occurs naturally, but
it's not impossible.>

name: Pyroballs
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Balloon Monster
Mainly lives in Fire Dragon Mountain

You've probably already figured
out what it is if you're not stupid.
Still, the allure of curiosity can
make one try the most dangerous things.

Do not pop under any circumstances.>
<反撃拡張:破裂カウンター>

name: Artefar
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン>
<text:Flame Monster
Mainly lives in Fire Dragon Mountain

A being similar to a spirit.
It appears when the ambient Mana 
contains attributes of the land.
This one is Fire, so it's a flame monster.

Though some insists it's a "butt monster".>

name: Magmaimai
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン,boss>
<text:Snail Monster
Encountered in Fire Dragon Mountain

A giant snail that lurks in the
scorching earth. Its shell is likened
to a mountain, and its body to lava,
making it akin to a volcano.

It is said that a similar monster was
once participant to a Calamity, but
that is of no relevance to this world.>

name: Fire Dragons' Apex
note:
<CategoryKey:トーリオン,boss>
<text:Dragon Monster
Encountered at Fire Dragon Apex

Dragons are known to be a race that is
unparalleled, but so are dragon people.

And sometimes, there exists those
who surpass the unparalleled further.>

name: ▼Signine
note: <NoBookData>

name: Floating Jellyfish
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Jellyfish Monster
Mainly lives in Shuva Ocean

Because it stores Thunder in its body,
it resists Thunder and is weak to
Earth, making it an outlier among
aquatic monsters.>

name: Ouchies
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Soft-bodied Monster
Mainly lives in Shuva Ocean

Its slimy body can deflect impacts and 
even magic, but it is very vulnerable 
to Thunder attacks.>

name: Anmony
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Soft-bodied Monster
Mainly lives in Shuva Ocean

A shell-like monster that floats 
through the air. It is said to not have
come from the sea, but rather the
dark sky above.>

name: Rogue Maggot
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Maggot Monster
Mainly lives in Shuva Ocean

The larvae of the fly monster.
Appears and breeds in places with
an abundance of dead flesh.

They move in groups and gather around
a piece of meat to feast.
Many adventurers find it disgusting.>

name: Flyder
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Fly Monster
Mainly lives in Shuva Ocean

An adult maggot monster.
Stores high magical power in its 
body to cast Wind magic.

Flies collect carrion and build 
pillars for their larvae. 
This is a noble activity necessary 
for raising children, but it seems 
strange to onlookers.>

name: That Which Touched the Universe
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ,boss>
<text:Soft-bodied Monster
Encountered in Shuva Ocean

The Anmony that set off for the sea
of Parlates became larger, shed off 
its shell, and became somewhat strange.

Now it looks up into the sky
of its hometown. 
Beyond that sky, lies the truth.>

name: Sissors
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Crab Monster
Mainly lives on the Solitary Island

Although it is a very small monster, 
it has sharp pincers, a hard shell, 
and excellent mobility, 
so don't let your guard down.>

name: Dirt Leech
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Leech Monster
Mainly lives on the Solitary Island

A giant sea leech.
Not only does it suck blood, but it
also injects a paralyzing venom.

It can be found floating in the sea.
It might stick to your body if
you're swimming around.>

name: Coralhead
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Fish Monster
Mainly lives on the Solitary Island

Looks like coral growing off some rocks,
but it's actually a fish monster with
a similar-looking shell.

There are many dangers in the sea,
so it camouflages itself as such.>

name: Treasure Chest Monster
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ,boss>
<text:Trap Monster
Encountered on the Solitary Island

An upright humanoid treasure chest.
Exudes a strange and eerie atmosphere.

Surprisingly, it doesn't use magic
and elects to overwhelm its prey
with martial arts.>

name: Who?
note: <NoBookData>

name: Sea Lavish
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Rubble Monster
Mainly lives in the Floating Ruins

A monster that takes refuge in the
rubble that sinks into the sea.
Must be comfy.>

name: Shadow Crow
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Crow Monster
Mainly lives in the Floating Ruins

It has a black body like a shadow 
monster, and acts as if it is one.

It hides its body's weaknesses.
What a smart monster.>

name: Kokototo
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Lost Child Monster
Mainly lives in the Floating Ruins

The contents of a trap monster.
It lost its treasure chest and is
now wandering aimlessly on its feet.

It won't become hostile if you don't
annoy it, but once it does, it will
follow you to the ends of the earth.
Escape is difficult.
Fighting is the only option.>

name: Maiden's Familiar
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ,boss>
<text:Water Monster
Encountered at the Shrine of Depths

A magical creature born from water,
protecting the life of the shrine maiden.

The Lord refuses to be visited.
Is there perhaps some secret?>

name: Undert
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Bird Monster
Mainly lives in Sous Shuva

A strange bird living on the ocean floor.
Swims as if it were flying.

It apparently can also live on land, 
but it becomes immobile when it is 
tied to something.>

name: Chrome Jellyfish
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Jellyfish Monster
Mainly lives in Sous Shuva

They have extremely hard metallic flesh, 
and no blade can penetrate even their 
soft-looking parts.

Some of them can speak.>

name: Opytarasus
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Snake Woman Monster
Mainly lives in habitats in Sous Shuva

A Snake Woman that lives in the sea.
Unlike their terrestrial counterparts, 
they tend to be gentle, but their 
reclusive nature remains the same.

They are very similar to mermaids. 
If you point that out to them, 
they will get angry.>

name: Deep Sea Terror
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ,boss>
<text:Centipede Monster
Encountered in Sous Shuva

A large centipede adapted to the deep.
It fell from another star and sank
to the bottom of the sea, kickstarting
its evolutionary adaptation.>

name: Mefka
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Shark Monster
Mainly lives in Shuva Hollow

A race said to have power comparable
to the dragons. Usually lives in the
sea, but can swim through the air
and can appear on land as well.

They lure males they like and take 
them captive by force. Do not be
fooled by their appearance.>

name: That Shark From Before
note: <NoBookData>

name: Malekotama
note:
<CategoryKey:シニュニーヌ>
<text:Mystery Monster
Mainly lives on the Hidden Island

A strange-looking being.
It is said to be a type of spirit,
but there is no basis for saying this.>

name: ▼Virea
note: <NoBookData>

name: Octa Device
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Machine Monster
Mainly lives in the Sky Ruins

天空遺跡の上層を守る機械
侵入者を発見すると追跡を初め
搭載した兵器により破壊を試みる>

name: Esmine
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Machine Monster
Mainly lives in the Sky Ruins

高性能な機械人形
人間に近い特徴を持つ
例えば、体表は人肌のように柔らかい

採精のための機能を多数備えている
機械とて、マナが必要なのだ>

name: Ornishia
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Bird Monster
Mainly lives in the Hanging Gardens

雌だけが存在する種族
つがいとなる他の種族の雄を探し続ける
特に人間は相性がいいという>

name: Manawraith Mutant
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア,boss>
<text:Mana Monster
Encountered in the Hanging Gardens

完全な存在たるマナレイスが逸脱し
一体の魔物へと変異した状態
故にこれはもはや完全ではない

完全が、そうでなくなる可能性があるのならば
それは完全と言えるのだろうか>

name: Sienoke
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Machine Monster
Mainly lives in the Sky Ruins Lower Layer

野生の機械生命体
国によってはカザドーと呼ばれる

戦闘を嫌う、友好的な個体が存在し
人と共に暮らすこともある>

name: Kreschi
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Machine Monster
Mainly lives in the Sky Ruins Lower Layer

野生の機械生命体
国によってはカザドーと呼ばれる

群れて現れることが多いため危険だが
素材を集めやすい一面もある>

name: Farzaan
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Machine Monster
Mainly lives in the Sky Ruins Lower Layer

野生の機械生命体
国によってはカザドーと呼ばれる

両脚を掴めば共に空を飛べるが
どこへ向かうか分からないため
そんなことをしてはならない>

name: Mechanical Twin
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア,boss>
<text:Machine Monster
Encountered in the Lower Layer

常に二体で行動する機械人形
そのために双子と称される

本来は一つの存在であったといい
血よりも確かな繋がりがある>

name: Tetetoto
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Lost Child Monster
Mainly lives in the Ruins Treasure Trove

罠の魔物として知られる存在の中身
収まるべき箱を探し歩く

宝箱の中には宝がある
よって自身も宝なのだと確信しており
その類に親近感を覚えている>

name: Dud
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Bomb Monster
Mainly lives in the Alien Ruins

自律する不発弾
衝撃により大爆発を引き起こすが
それを恐れず、一気に破壊してしまえば
安全に処理できる>

name: Elemium
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Liquid Monster
Mainly lives in the Landfill

炎を恐れぬ可燃性の液体
何故だか自ら熱源に近づき
そのまま燃え尽きることもある

危険に惹かれる年頃なのだろうか>

name: Esroar
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Machine Monster
Mainly lives in the Landfill

朽ち果てた機械人形
それでも自我は失っておらず
何かを求めて、さまよっている>

name: Landfill Nemesis
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア,boss>
<text:Insect Monster
Encountered in the Landfill

力をつけ、姿を変えた宿敵
物陰に潜むことはなくなり
正面切っての戦闘で敵対者を討つ

宿敵には言い知れぬ恐怖を覚えるものだが
こうも変われば、そうでもなくなる>

name: Belr Chimera
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア>
<text:Hybrid Monster
Mainly lives in the Hybrid Lab

高度な魔力と知能を持つ魔物
そのいずれも、人の身では理解できない

極めて稀な、自然に生まれた魔法生物であり
様々な研究の対象となっているが
価値ある成果を得た例はない>

name: Shadow of the Stars, Kaamos
note:
<CategoryKey:ヴィーレア,boss>
<text:Spirit of Darkness
Encountered at the Wind Furnace

To return home, she concocted a plan.
The plan to destroy this world. 

She lurked in and exploited the dark,
angering the Child of Light.>

name: ▼Ainoa
note: <NoBookData>

name: Igjum
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Scavenger Monster
Mainly lives in the Star Corpse

ゴミ漁りはゴミを漁る故にそう呼ばれるが
実際のところ、彼らが漁るのは
そればかりではない

死すれば遺る
それをゴミとは呼べぬだろう>

name: Shadow Murder
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Shadow Monster
Mainly lives in the Star Corpse

死の臭いが漂う場所に住み着く魔物
それを濁す生者を見つけると
影に紛れ、命を狙う>

name: Dark Dome
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Nest Monster
Mainly lives in the Star Corpse

闇を蓄えた不気味な魔物
その穴から内側を覗き込めば
名状しがたい何かが、こちらを覗き返す>

name: Deadthorn Avian
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア,boss>
<text:Army of the Night
Encountered at the Star Corpse

狂気の夜の影響により現れた魔物
闇の性質の一つ、死を宿している

闇に魅入られた主を野放しにすれば
パーラテスは遠からず、このような存在で
埋め尽くされるだろう>

name: Nightwraith
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Darkness Monster
Mainly lives at the Throne of Creation

狂気の夜から零れ落ちた闇
夜の軍勢の尖兵である>

name: Communicator Overlooking the Sea
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア,boss>
<text:Ghost Monster
Encountered at the Throne of Creation

いつ頃からそこにいたのだろうか
海の果てで、ただ何かを待つ存在

この世界は繭であり、繭の中には世界がある
世界には繭が漂い、その中にまた世界がある>

name: Ash Chick
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Bird Monster
Mainly lives in The Lost Ordomarr

燃え尽きた不死鳥
今でも再生の力は残しており
意外と元気に生きている>

name: Auribile
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Viscera Monster
Mainly lives in The Lost Ordomarr

その地のマナの在り方が正常でないとき
どこからともなく湧き出る魔物
その姿は悍ましく、臓腑に似ている>

name: Darion
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Lizard Monster
Mainly lives in The Lost Ordomarr

移動のたび、その環境に合わせて
体色を変え続ける魔物
本来、体表は何色をしているのか
確認できた者はまだいない>

name: Night Velmel
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア>
<text:Flower Monster
Mainly lives in The Lost Ordomarr

夜に似た色の花
その性格は、意外にも明るい

死をもたらす猛毒の花粉を持つ
仲良くなろうなどと思わないこと>

name: Star Lunacy
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア,boss>
<text:Darkness Spirit
Encountered at The Lost Ordomarr

The Lord of Reason who once walked
alongside the path of the stars.
More than anything, she was disappointed
in herself, and drifted from her path.
She simply dreams of the night back home.

It seems she is no longer sane.>

name: Cocoon of the Cradle
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア,boss>
<ShowDataBook>
<text:Cocoon Drifting in the Sea
Encountered at the Astral Cocoon

Many sparks slumber within Ordowald,
and all of them could lead to destruction.

This is one of those such sparks.>

name: One Who Devours the Cocoon
note:
<CategoryKey:アイノア,boss>
<text:The Universe within the Cocoon
Encountered at the Astral Cocoon

That universe is a world of nothingness.
All attributes are mixed equally together,
and after the rainbow encounter,
they eventually lose all color.

If they are unleashed, they will cover
the world as it exists, and then not even
a trace of the old world will remain.>

name: ▼Memory Space
note: <NoBookData>

name: Prismforge
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Mana Monster
Mainly lives in the Sea of Rainbows

属性が入り乱れる場所に漂うマナ
魔法生物の一種である

これは自然にしか生まれない
属性の力は何者にも御しきれないのだ>

name: Alvemagus
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Succubus Monster
Mainly lives in the Memory of Solitude

アルヴと呼ばれる夜魔は特に危険で
魔力も魅力も卓越している

そうした夜魔の多くは老齢である
それを指摘することが有効な場合がある>

name: Tobari
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Owl Monster
Mainly lives in the Memory of Sacrifice

東方の島国シキノワの忍者
覆ったものを透明にする羽毛を持ち
自身だけでなく、獲物をも隠す>

name: Cucuclack
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Insect Monster
Mainly lives in the Memory of Loss

マナを求めた結果、人型となった宿敵
嫌悪感は薄れたような気がするが
元がどうだったか、忘れてはいけない>

name: Spectral
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Ghost Monster
Mainly lives in the Memory of Disappointment

スペクトラルは何者かの死後の姿ではない
より概念的な、死の魔物であり
通常の幽霊とは一味違う>

name: Hallucinion
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Mushroom Monster
Mainly lives in the Memory of Melancholy

茸の魔物の髪に似た柄は伸縮自在で
広げて伸ばせば天幕のようになる
雄を見つければ、その内に閉じ込める
それが彼女の狩りである>

name: Sky Ruler
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Bird Monster
Mainly lives in the Memory of Seifu

空の支配者たる種の魔物
尋常ならざる視力を持っており
雲の上から地上の様子を見るという>

name: Spacewalk Dragonfish
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:Fish Monster
Encountered at the Sea of Rainbows

パーラテスの海を泳ぐ竜魚
宇宙的な力を獲得している

これは印象的な記憶である
とある誰かが、どこかで挑み
苦戦を強いられたのかもしれない>

name: Sangmung
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Leech Monster
Mainly lives in Caunis Merri

暗い海を泳ぐ蛭の類
血を求め、それが流れるものを探すが
そうした獲物がそこにはいない>

name: Anterium
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Soft-bodied Monster
Mainly lives in Caunis Merri

暗い空にいる貝に似た魔物
海でも同じような魔物を見かけるが
こちらが源流、宇宙的存在である>

name: Unipiscis
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Insect Monster
Mainly lives in Caunis Merri

パーラテスの海にいる巨大な虫
光属性を蓄えており、それを吐き出し
更に光の魔法をも放つ>

name: Forenless
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Humanoid Monster
Mainly lives in Caunis Merri

秘匿された真理を知り、狂気に堕ちた魔法使い
話は通じる。しかし心が通じない

探求の果てに滅びの定めを知れば
絶望し、智を欠くのも致し方ないこと>

name: Eureka
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Corpse Monster
Mainly lives in Caunis Merri

至高の頭脳を持つとされる魔物
雷に打たれ覚醒したのだ

智慧を求め、倣ったものの末路などは
語るまでもないだろう>

name: Okotama
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域>
<text:Mystery Monster
Mainly lives in Caunis Merri

奇妙な姿をした存在
精霊の一種であると信じられているが
精霊たちは、その説に異を唱える>

name: Uneven Horns, Kannryuua
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:Lord of Reason
Encountered at the Memory of Solitude

The flame succubus ruling over Torion.
Her very existence has enthralled
everyone on the star, and has gained
unparalleled support as a Lord of Reason.

Though she has no interest in being
treated as such, she nonetheless is
pleased with the benefits it brings.>

name: Thundercurse Shroud, Valco
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:Lord of Reason
Encountered at the Memory of Sacrifice

The thunder spirit watching over Kertailt.
He quietly watches over the residents,
and nothing more.

However, the Flower Fairies know of
his support and is very attached to him.>

name: Mad Hunt, Muracca
note:
<反撃拡張:拘束返し>
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:Lord of Reason
Encountered at the Memory of Loss

An active hunter on Talvirar, an
essential presence on the harsh star.
The residents survive thanks to her
and her companions' hard work.

Is a big eater despite the star
suffering food shortages, so she
absolutely must be the head hunter.>

name: Eternal Stagnation, Kilma
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:Lord of Reason
Encountered at the Memory of Disappointment

A monster living quietly on Signine.
Does nothing for her star, knowing
this is proof of its everlasting peace.

Dislikes having her peace disturbed.
Hates having secrets exposed even more.>

name: Sword of Slaughter, Luora
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:Lord of Reason
Encountered at the Memory of Melancholy

An adventurer traveling through Ront.
The star is new and unexplored,
and there is much to still learn.

She's an avid problem solver, so
she's often feared by problem causers.>

name: Sage of Karmic Ode, Tyvar
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:Lord of Reason
Encountered at the Memory of Seifu

The Wind spirit that maintains Virea.
Should Tyvar's existence cease,
the Sky Ruins would go down with him.

He should've been the one with the most
followers out of all the Lords, but
few residents even know he exists.>

name: Abyssal Light, Lesslie
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:Memory Adrift in the Sea of Stars
Encountered at Caunis Merri

A being drawn here through a connection.
She knows the inevitable future,
but chose to remain in that world
to resist the incoming destruction.

Even now, she may be performing
such heroic deeds within Ordowald.>

name: Witch of Creation, Tahati
note:
<CategoryKey:記憶領域,boss>
<text:The Creator of Parlates
Encountered at Domus Caunis

A magician who lived in the Age of Myth,
and in turn embodied that power.

On that day of destruction she swore
to create an eternal haven.>
